  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: d01fd2d64a9249049aaa77d5c12a82fe, type: 3}
  m_Name: Question 21
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  questionText: Which of the following types of change occurs during sublimation?
  referenceImage: {fileID: 0}
  explanationText: Sublimation is the process of conversion of a solid substance
    into its vapour state upon heating. No new chemical substance is formed, and
    the vapours get deposited back into the solid state upon cooling. Hence, it is 
    a physical change.
  options:
  - Irreversible change
  - Chemical change
  - Physical change
  - Permanent change
  correctOptionIndex: 2
